UPDATE:PREDEYPOYMENT PROPER WAY
First make sure you already have virutalenv on your machine not the project folder
get it with: pip install virtualenv

Then to use it on this project
cd RUCourseMaps
#virutalenv venv #you dont need to do this unless you dont see the venv folder
next start the venv
.\venv\Scripts\activate   or for bash it's
source venv/bin/activate
pip install - r requirements.txt #do this in your virtualenv
then your gtg to run the app

//////run app in venv/////
.\venv\Scripts\activate   or for bash it's
source venv/bin/activate
pip install venv
pip install Flask
pip install beautifulsoup4
deactivate    #when you want to stop virtual enviroment

/////start the application////
#cd in to rucoursemaps
python app.py
#then go to localhost:5000

/////for cywin users
 /cygdrive/c/Python27/python.exe app.py

 ///for deployment///
 start venv
 heroku login 		#assumes you already have herokudev toolkit installed
 pip install gunicorn
 gunicorn -b 127.0.0.1:4000 app:app



